(12, 9, '2011-02-02 20:41:50', '2011-02-02 20:41:50', '<a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/smLeaf_Green11.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-270" title="smLeaf_Green1" src="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/smLeaf_Green11.jpg" alt="Leaf" width="250" height="333" /></a>Diesel-powered vehicles continue to have a bright future in light of recent political, technological, and economical developments.  The reputation of diesel engines has shifted from being harmful to the environment to an appealing alternative for its fuel efficiency.\r\n\r\nNew technologies made this transition possible by significantly reducing the amount of emissions produced by diesel engines, a trend that is being reinforced by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) in attempt to address the air quality challenges facing America today.', 'Environment', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'environment', '', '', '2012-07-03 10:57:37', '2012-07-03 15:57:37', '', 0, 'http://victoryblue.squareminc.com/?page_id=12', 0, 'page', '', 0),
