(399, 49, '2013-05-23 11:57:12', '2013-05-23 16:57:12', 'Project will provide bulk loading 24/7 and packaging of API Certified Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF)\r\n\r\nPhoenix, AZ. — Victory Blue is proud to announce the opening of their new Diesel Exhaust Fluid blending and packaging facility. This facility adds a key component to Victory’s highly efficient multimode supply chain.  In keeping with Victory’s aggressive expansion in the DEF market, this facility is strategically located in a world class facility with the capability to distribute over 20 million gallons of DEF per year. This marks the 4th time in 2013 for Victory to announce a new facility opening. Victory is committed to providing the highest quality API certified  fluid and customer service in the industry. \r\n\r\nAbout DEF (Diesel Exhaust Fluid) – With the EPA mandate to reduce NOx emissions in diesel engines, SCR (Selective Catalytic Reduction) equipped engines have become the standard for eliminating the majority of Nitrogen Oxide (NOx) emissions. SCR systems use a solution of 32.5% Urea and 67.5% deionized water to treat the exhaust stream and reduce the NOx to simple nitrogen and water vapor out of the exhaust pipe.  This technology will also be used to reduce emissions in the Off Road, Agricultural, Marine, and Locomotive industries over the next several years. \r\n\r\nAbout Victory Blue, LLC- Victory, a Texas based company, produces Victory Blue DEF (Diesel Exhaust Fluid), an API certified fluid complying with ISO 22241 to reduce NOx emissions in SCR equipped diesel engines. Using ultrapure water and technical grade Urea, Victory Blue surpasses the industry standards for purity and quality.  Victory Blue has an international reach with production facilities coast to coast in North America.  (dev.govictoryblue.com)\r\n', 'Victory Blue DEF now Open in Phoenix', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '314-revision-3', '', '', '2013-05-23 11:57:12', '2013-05-23 16:57:12', '', 314, 'http://dev.govictoryblue.com/2013/05/23/314-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(400, 49, '2013-03-08 09:30:19', '2013-03-08 15:30:19', 'Stockton, CA, March 7, 2013– Victory Blue announces a new Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) production/packaging facility in Stockton, CA. with the Grand Opening set for March 13, 2013.\r\nVictory Blue is now producing and distributing Victory Blue DEF from its new facility at the Port of Stockton. Victory produces and packages for companies that include Cummins and Valvoline.\r\n\r\nJason Lower, Executive VP at Victory said: "This facility helps to solidify our distribution network on the West Coast. We are confident that our new Stockton California facility will provided a much needed supply solution to the region. The "Victory Model" has proven to be successful in regions across the country and we are certain that our drive to provide impeccable quality and service to our new customers in California will bring further success.  We are proud to bring jobs to the area and be a contributor to the ongoing efforts to improve air quality through cleaner emissions for future generations."\r\n\r\nVictory Blue\'s production facility in Stockton has 24/7 bulk loading, as well as a full inventory of totes, drums, jugs, and a line of equipment for the end user. Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) is a new product required by many heavy-duty trucks, pickups, SUVs, Vans, agricultural, construction and forestry equipment delivered after January 2010. DEF is used to destroy harmful emissions in the exhaust and meet the EPA\'s latest strict environmental standards.\r\n\r\nDEF is non-hazardous and consists of 67.5% de-ionized water and 32.5% urea, and is used in combination with Selective Catalytic Reduction (SCR) technology. It is sprayed into the exhaust and combines with a catalyst to break down NOx (a harmful pollutant) into nitrogen and water.\r\n\r\nIn January 2010 emissions legislation came into force which requires diesel vehicles to significantly reduce harmful emissions of NOx and particulate matter. A good way to meet these standards is to use SCR and DEF.  Daimler, PACCAR, Volvo, Mack, Isuzu, Hino, Ford, GM, Navistar, AGCO, Case, John Deere, and others are using SCR,\r\n\r\nSCR technology offers many benefits, most importantly great fuel efficiency. On top of this, owners of SCR vehicles and equipment will enjoy greater reliability and a longer oil change interval, all of which adds up to impressive savings over the life of the vehicle.\r\n', 'New Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) facility in Stockton, CA. ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '306-revision-6', '', '', '2013-03-08 09:30:19', '2013-03-08 15:30:19', '', 306, 'http://dev.govictoryblue.com/2013/03/08/306-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
