go through a new phone and a new laptop in two years. But what to do with the old electronics? Throwing them away can cause serious issues in landfills, since they contain toxic chemicals like lead, mercury, beryllium, cadmium, and even sometimes arsenic. Recycling is part of the three R’s, but recycling E-waste is especially important!\r\n\r\nBeing green has never been easier. There are <a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/2013/08/16/5-easy-ways-you-can-help-the-environment/">other ways for you to help the environment</a>, but it’s nice to know that being green isn’t just restricted to being at home. Luckily, with SCR technology and <a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/about-def/">diesel exhaust fluid</a>, it’s also never been easier to drive a clean, green car. Diesels burn clean when they use DEF, so check out <a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/order-online/">Victory Blue</a> today!', 'The Top 7 Ways to Go Green in the Office', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '525-revision-2', '', '', '2013-08-27 16:06:08', '2013-08-27 21:06:08', '', 525, 'http://dev.govictoryblue.com/2013/08/27/525-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
