(564, 49, '2013-09-12 14:00:54', '2013-09-12 19:00:54', 'Representing your company on the internet is one of the most important things you can do to grow your business. On social media, you’re able to provide free advertising and better customer service. On your personal site, you’re able to incorporate SEO to get more site hits. But do you really need to list the locations of your business on your site? If you’ve gone through <a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/">our site</a> then you probably know what our answer will be: YES. Having several locations says a lot about your company, which is why it is important that you show which locations you have and where they are. Read on to discover the three things that having several locations says about your company.\r\n\r\n<center><a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/map.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-565" alt="map" src="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/map-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></center><b>Versatility</b>\r\n\r\nThe first thing that having several locations (and showing them on your site) says about your company is that you’re versatile. Your company is able to adapt to the situation that your customers have. For example, if you have a customer in California who just opened a branch in New York, your multiple locations would provide you with the ability to continue working with them. This may seem obvious to you, but it is a subtle implication to your customers. A locations map lets your customers know that you’re there to serve their needs, wherever their needs are. Your versatility as a company is a selling point. It’s important for you to display to your customers that your company can take care of them wherever they are, which is what having multiple locations says about your company.\r\n\r\n<b>Durability</b>\r\n\r\nThe second thing that several locations says about your company is that your company is durable. If you are able to expand from your initial site, then your strategy is obviously working. Durability doesn’t just mean that your company can handle the regular ups and downs of business, however. Several locations lends your company a lot of business credit because it means that your actual business model is durable. You are able to succeed with multiple locations and therefore your company is trustworthy. It is easier for your customer to trust you when you’ve proven that you can maintain multiple locations.\r\n\r\n<b>Ambition </b>\r\n\r\nHaving several locations shows that your company has ambition. Your company wouldn’t have expanded without ambition and ambition is definitely something that you can sell to your customers. What better way to show that you are dedicated to them than by showing that you have the ambition to match their needs and to succeed in multiple locations? You prove to your customers that you have the drive to succeed when you have several locations.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/locations/">Victory Blue has several locations</a> for our DEF facilities and we’re especially proud of the recent ones that we’ve opened. If you have any questions, whether it\'s about locations, businesses, or <a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/about-def/">DEF</a>, please contact us!', 'The 3 Things Having Several Locations Says About Your Company', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-3-things-having-several-locations-says-about-your-company', '', '', '2013-09-12 14:00:54', '2013-09-12 19:00:54', '', 0, 'http://dev.govictoryblue.com/?p=564', 0, 'post', '', 0),
