es Fahrenheit then the shelf life will be two years. Otherwise, it is typically one year though you can always contact your DEF supplier to find out the exact timelines.\r\n\r\n<center><a href="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tote2.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-246" alt="storage of DEF" src="http://dev.govictoryblue.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tote2.jpg" width="250" height="250" /></a></center>\r\n<p align="center"></p>', 'Three Questions for Handling and Storage of DEF', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '580-revision-11', '', '', '2013-09-17 11:23:57', '2013-09-17 16:23:57', '', 580, 'http://dev.govictoryblue.com/2013/09/17/580-revision-11/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
